name: Rainbow Vortex Fumed Pendant
description: Rainbow vortex style with an elongated tear-drop shape and unique heart bale. 24K gold & .999 silver fuming creates an exceptional range of colors. Half-knot macrame using strong, soft hemp. Several brightly colored semi-precious stones including imperial jasper alongside Czech glass beads. Figure-eight clasp with removable drawstrings. Length: 18" (fixed) Pendant Size: 1" x 2" Borosilicate: Freddy Om Faerron

name: Steal Your Face Heady Opal Pendant
description: "Steal Your Face" honeycomb glass pendant with well centered, holographic floating opal. Gorgeous array of blues, greens and light browns flow in a dreamlike state over this HUGE skull. Originally designed by Owsley Stanley and rendered by Bob Thomas, Steal your Face pendants or "Stealies" are an ode to the Grateful Dead and their legacy of trippy, "mind-blowing" music. Size: 3.2" x 2.4" Weight: 4.5 oz Borosilicate: Bobbo Glass

name: Bombara Break Pendant
description: Bombora, an aboriginal term for a wave that breaks over a shallow reef, describes the sunshine, kelp, and blue-green churning waters that inspire these colors. This curling wave vortex 24K gold & .999 silver fumed glass pendant is perfectly circular and backed by a dark black bail. Sparkled magnifiers accentuate the building of that perfect wave. Half-knot macrame using strong, medium soft hemp combines the perfect surfer style cording with green fire agate, kyanite, AB Czech glass, aventurine and shiny onyx rounds. Figure-eight matte onyx clasp with removable drawstrings. Length: 21" (fixed) Pendant Size: 1.4" x 1.8" Borosilicate: Alex Garvie

name: Soleil Elemental Pendant
description: Earth. Wind. Water. Fire. A perfectly circular, sun-shaped vortex hides spectral blue bursts that connect with a wavy exterior. Super clean, uniquely shaped air traps alternate sizes in a well spaced pattern. Hidden colors emerge on a dark background or in the sunlight. Half-knot macrame using strong, soft hemp includes a matching triple helix. Figure-eight matte onyx clasp with removable drawstrings. Length: Custom Adjustable Pendant Size: 1.65" x 2" Borosilicate: Phil Hackman

name: G-Switch 49 Pendant
description:
As close to perfect as pendants come, this heavily fumed 24K gold, half switch implosion glass pendant is clean, bubble free and full of depth and color. 

Black onyx, gold freshwater pearls and faceted lampwork wheels.

Half-knot macrame with heavy duty, naturally rough hemp in a choker size.

Length: 16" <i>(fixed choker)<i/>
Pendant Size: 1.1" x 1.4"
Borosilicate: Conan Phillips

name: Dot Implosion Flower Pendant
description:
Over one-hundred blossoming petals fumed on this circular dot implosion glass pendant. "Gerbera" colored exterior petals terminate in a soft tan center. Solid black backing and bail pop this autumn flower.

Size: 1.875" x 2.875"
Weight: 2.6 oz
Borosilicate: Charley Reynolds

name: Atomic Chaos Pendant
description: Translucent glowing lines fumed in entropy. With movement, light catches along these lines in beautifully small electron-like specks and traces the patterns as if powered by the sun. Half-knot macrame with symmetrical triple helix on both sides. Strong, soft hemp with custom lampwork beads by Andrew Grey. Freshwater pearls, peach aventurine, carnelion, amber shell, and glass discs round out this atomic scheme. Length: 14" - 22" (adjustable) Pendant Size: 1.4" x 1.8" Borosilicate: Joshua Tree Glass

name: Sacred Eye Dichro Pendant
description: "Dichro" is short term for dichroic, meaning two-colored. Special metal, laid within glass, splits a beam of light into two different wavelengths (colors) which gives this pendant it's holographic nature. The design is laser etched by removing parts of the material and leaving the rest. Varying shades of blues and purples are emerge as this pendant moves with light. Half-knot macrame with A/B Czech glass, shiny onyx, silver freshwater pearls and iridescent blue ovals on thin, very soft, waxed cotton cording. *Note* Slight dichro laser burn in the center. Only viewable from a very sharp angle, but is noticeable if trying to find. Length: 17" - 18" (fixed) Pendant Size: 1.1" x 1.65" Borosilicate: Matt Veazie

name: Futurismo Pendant
description: An absolute personal favorite! Twenty-two beads, four double helixes, two single beside half-knot macrame on thin, very soft, waxed cotton cording. Interior hemp "guide-lines" create a duo-tone pattern on the drawstrings and behind the beads. An exceptional assortment of natural and hand-made elements compliments a non-backed circular glass pendant with reverse magnifier that allows for your clothing color to tint the reverse adding depth and versatility. Inspired by a futurism style, the colors coalesce in a wonderfully eccentric pattern, right down to the bail. Highly adjustable necklace features: Brass, tiger's eye amber shell, blue aventurine, two types of A/B Czech glass, gold freshwater pearl, amber glass, blue pearlescent poly, and natural abalone lentil. Length: 14" - 22" (adjustable) Pendant Size: 1.2" x 1.5" Borosilicate: Chris Boudreaux

name: Floret Bloom Pendant
description: Highly realistic down to the last detail, the well laid pistols, petals, leaves and soft pastel colors bloom in this flower glass pendant. Half-knot macrame on strong, soft hemp. Matching pastel colored glass, ceramic and pearlescent plastic beads draw upon the most subtle colors of the flower. Sliding clasp allows for adjustable fit. Length: 16" - 28" (adjustable) Pendant Size: 1" x 1.7" Borosilicate: Allison Stardust

name: Perennial Moments Pendant
description: Pastels petals in green blue and yellow exude life from this perfectly round dot implosion glass pendant. No backing with a clear exterior, improve the overall color and look. Half-knot macrame with black onyx and antiqued turquoise twists. * This piece has been broken in, meaning it's ultra soft and extremely flexible... but is also slightly "worn" as a result. This is natural and happens to all necklaces over time, as they come to fit the wearer. As you can see it still looks beautiful! * Length: 16" - 19" (fixed) Pendant Size: 1.3" x 1.9" Borosilicate: Amir Shawn

name: Coral Aquarium Pendant
description:
Black and blue dot stacks encircle a clear center lens and terminate near the dual color bale. Bubbly orange, white and green "corals" sprout feelers while enveloping a shadowed celadon blue backing that makes this this coral "tank" seem complete.

Size: 1.6" x 2.4"
Weight: 1.6 oz
Borosilicate: Andrew Rose

name: Antigua Swirl Dot Implosion Pendant
description: Very clean, swirled implosion in orange, black and white wraps around well placed turquoise dots. Continuous bail wraps over the top for an uninterrupted look. Half-knot macrame with dyed quartzite, white onyx and turquoise ceramic on thin, very soft, waxed cotton cording. Length: 18" (fixed) Pendant Size: 1.2" x 1.4" Borosilicate: Conan Phillips

name: Wyvern Stones Dragon Eye Pendant
description: Stunning blue and green iris on this realistic dragon's eye with raised bump lid. With the reflection of fire in its eyes, a gripping stare takes hold and you're sucked into its allurement. Half-knot macrame using 10 strong, soft hemp cords makes for a very thick, comfortable necklace. Green rounds and nuggets of unknown origin are magnificent shades of dragon scales. Length: 17" - 20" (fixed) Pendant Size: 1.75" x 1.65" Borosilicate: Jamie Leigh

name: Bubblecomb Pendant
description: Hollow, trapped bubble honeycomb cleanly set over a clear backing. perfectly circular glass pendant Minimal, delightful colors resemble underwater air bubbles clung to glass on this. Great size to weigh ratio. Size: 1.9" round Weight: 1.2 oz Borosilicate: Stephen Mugler

name: Stellar Collapse Pendant
description: A hydrogen fusion in glass, this blue-hot giant is shedding its outer layers as its core collapses over time. Gorgeous, deep blues are clouded throughout a small expanse of space. Three small opals shine from within the teardrop clear at the bottom of this circular pendant. Heavy duty 8 cord, half-knot macrame using very soft hemp features white onyx and lapis lazuli. Single bead clasp with knotted extensions. Length: 16" - 20" adjustable Pendant Size: 1.4" x 2.7"

name: Cork Plug Glass Stash Jars
description: Whimsically hand-crafted, cork-able glass jars for your favorite items; smoke-able or otherwise! three different styles to choose from: windswept white, red or clear fume. Size: 1.75" x 3"(rough) Weight: 2oz Borosilicate: Steven Mugnos

name: Wet Stone Walk Pendant
description:
White stone exterior dots the surface of a small well of wet river rocks below. Strong blues, a touch of green and a deep purple backing give this piece the type of hand-made zen a glass pendant should have.

Size: 1.5" x 2.1
Weight: 1.2 oz
Borosilicate: Jay Shatsky

name: B&W Dabber Dishes
description: Sophisticated black and white glass dabber dishes with skillet handles. Don't dab out of a little plastic jar when you can save your stash with these. Heat the handle to squeeze out every last drop. Size: ~ 1 -2" round (rough) Weight: ~1 - 2 oz (rough) Borosilicate: Ryan Miller

name: Switching Tracks Retti Pendant
description: The bustling commotion of light and dark orange combines with white as this reticello spirals into an empty center termination. This perfectly circular clear glass pendant is very clean, brightly colored and completely duo-tone. A white bail accents the dominant orange. Skinny half-knot macrame on ultra soft, bright white cotton with white onyx, painted orange swirl ceramic and dyed quartzite ruby rounds. Length: 17" - 21" (fixed) Pendant Size: 1.3" x 1.8" Borosilicate: Nolen Olive

name: Perplexed Edibles Pendant
description: Struggling from an existential crisis, this glass pendant can't decide exactly what it is! Deep oranges, yellow and green surrounded by teal blue and purple on this inverted teardrop shaped piece. "Pineapple-like" depressions and cross-hatching create a wonderful lens from which colors ebb and flow. The jump ring on the focal bead allows for it to be interchanged (no cutting necessary) with other necklaces if desired. Fire cleaned half-knot macrame using naturally rough hemp features pearl coin opals and orange coral rounds. The look of the cording looks slightly burned as a result of the fire cleaning. This creates a deeper, rougher look. Length: 16" - 19" (fixed) Size: 1" x 1.75" Borosilicate: Ian Grabber

name: Strange Hive Honeycomb Pendant
description: Densely colored, well saturated, hollow honeycomb glass pendant with matching set of six magnifiers. Oranges, purples, blues, greens envelop well shaped combs as they slow descend into madness. Backed with a winding sparkled blue lagoon, the reverse opens into a large bowl shape. Size: 1.7" round Weight: 1 oz Borosilicate: Jacob Garvin

name: Elfin Forest Spore Pendant
description: Fungi shaped fuming sporadically reaches in all directions looking to expand. A purple cloud of "spores" emanates from the surrounding area over-top the fruits. Backed with a dark purple and clear bail. Half-knot macrame using very soft, strong hemp features a single-bead clasp with matching wooden beads. Length: 16" - 19" (fixed) Pendant Size: 1" x 1.5" Created: Lincoln, Nebraska

name: Rogue Hive Pendant
description:
Ghostly fumed purple, amber and orange honeycomb with stinger and dual amber magnifiers on this hollow glass "bee" pendant. Chaotic combing giving way to heed of rumors that something is quite wrong at the hive.

Size: 2.3" x 2.75"
Weight: 1.25 oz
Borosilicate: Jacob Garvin

name: Dripping Honeycomb Pendant
description:
Gorgeous crystal clear amber glass, honeycomb-drip style pendant that seems to melt in your hands. Clean, strong drips covered in 24K gold and .999 silver fuming provide subtle, but striking contrast. These colors are accentuated by dark clothing and are nearly hidden when worn on white.

Size: 3.9" x 2.1"
Weight: 1.75 oz
Borosilicate: Kevin Bergesson

name: Seven Moons Dot Stack Pendant
description:
Dot stack pattern in three layers of seven, balanced well on a perfectly circular design. A clear bail tops translucent ocean blues & greens that coalesce through waves of sparkles and tan highlights. 

Half-knot macrame using bright white, ultra soft, cotton cord ties together the semi-precious stones Fancy Jasper, Moss Agate, Kyanite and Aquamarine. Figure- eight clasp with removable drawstrings.

Length: 18-19" (fixed)
Pendant Size: 1" x 1.6"
Borosilicate: Dave M.C.

name: Multi-Dimensional Beacon Pendant
description: A beacon from another place. Tan spikes (rounded) dotted with blue surround... Size: 1.8" x 2" Weight: 1.3 oz Borosilicate: Andrew Rose

name: Black Cherry Swirl Pendant
description:
Light blacks, off-white and glitter accentuate the dark, cherry red drops that surround the exterior of this circular "bottle cap" swirled glass pendant. Swirling flourishes terminated at a beautiful "sun" center.

Size: 1.85" x 2.5"
Weight: 1.45 oz
Borosilicate: Andrew Rose

name: Autumn Whirl Pendant
description: Inspiring paint-a-whirl enthusiasts everywhere, this earth-toned piece has mountains of depth, striking a balance of subtle, even muted colors. Off whites, not quite blacks and a light touch of green, yellow and blue in a sea of orange. Half-knot macrame using strong, soft hemp compliments the carnelion, fossil coral, bone, tiger's eye and smokey onyx that connect this piece with the earth. Figure- eight clasp with removable drawstrings. Length: 18" (fixed) Pendant Size: 1.5" x 1.9" Borosilicate: Andrew Gray

name: Greek Mosque Dot Stack Pendant
description: An outer layer of relaxed olive waves of three sparkle as they surround shimmering mosque (blue-green) rounds. A semi-opaque, midnight blue centerpiece, encircled by leaves and petals, conceals a fierce blue eye beneath. Clear backing, white highlights and a midnight blue barrel bail round out this beautiful, modern glass pendant. Size: 1.9" x 2.4" Weight: 2.125 oz Borosilicate: Jay Shatsky

name: Yoshi Egg Pendant
description: Inverted double dot pattern in warm blues and greens continuing through a reverse bale. The colors and pattern are reminiscent of the well known Super Mario Brother's character "Yoshi's" eggs. Half-knot macrame with symmetrical triple helix on both sides. Strong, soft hemp with speckled turquoise ceramic, translucent glass, plastic, dyed freshwater pearl, pearlescent plastic and aventurine twists. Length: 18-26" (adjustable) Pendant Size: 1.1" x 1.3" Borosilicate: Conan Phillips.

name: Alien Anemone Spiked Pendant
description: Slyme green spikes(rounded) dotted with black surround a clear center lens and run up and around the bail. Backed by sky blue with electric purple radiating from the base of the alien shaped anemone, the blue, green and yellow colors are quite unique and range somewhere between pastel and highlighter. Size: 1.75" x 2.4" Weight: 1.65 oz Borosilicate: Andrew Rose

name: Pink Polka Celebration Pendant
description:
White highlights shuffle through waltzing pink as it mingles towards a candy-stripped center swirl. Light, blue-green circles sparkle on the dance floor of this glass pendant.

Size: 1.7" x 2.3
Weight: 1.7 oz

name: Farewell K.S. Swirl Pendant
description: We're not in Kansas anymore... Warm colors of summer wheat, sunset, clouds and sky all swirled in a vortex that looks more like an oil panting than glass pendant. Dark purple bail and dotted backing. Size: 1.6" x 2.4" Weight: 1.6 oz Borosilicate: Jay Shatsky

name: Valknute of Scandinavia Necklace
description: Saint John's Arms, the Place of Interest Sign, Saint Hannes Cross, or Looped Square... whatever you call it, it's a beautiful symbol that has lasted throughout the ages. Hand-carved from carnelian stone, this beautifully macremed necklace details extensive knotting patterns accented simply with two matching, faced brass rounds secured symmetrically. Can be tied / cut to your length of choice! Length: 16" - 24" (fixed) Size: 3.2" x 2.4"

name: Osseous Fish Necklace
description: Dual carved fish in relief on this circular bone pendant. Matching engraved bone rounds with a round wood clasp on strong, soft hemp makes for completely natural look and feel. Length: 15" - 19" (fixed) Pendant Size: 1.1" x 1.1"

name: Desert Stream Lampwork Necklace
description: Choker style macrame necklace with three matching lampwork beads and engraved brass rondelles. The colors, style and size all attribute to its clean and sophisticated aesthetics. Length: 15 - 20" (fixed) Created: Lincoln, Nebraska

name: Turquoise Wire Wrap Pendent
description:
Finely polished, teardrop shaped turquoise stone centerpiece wire-wrapped in mixed gauge pink and silver metal. This personally-selected stone has lightning strike vein patterns and sits comfortably under a dual corkscrew bale.

Arrives with matching ribbon cord necklace.

Length: 18" - 20"
Pendant Size: 1.25" x 2.1"

Silver on silver... on silver.  This descending set of matching silver plated earrings features six silver plated rounds and geometric shapes that bear a slight resemblance to a yellow jacket bee (wasp). The flourishes on top add the illusion of small wings.

Matching set of earrings featuring hematite stars, hearts and rounds. Hematite is a lightweight, strong metal, that softly reflects light and has a very minor bit of magnetism.
Black on black for the rockstar.

name: Candy Store Faves Earrings
description: Inspired by the favorite candies of our youth...Swedish Fish, Twizzlers, Pixy Stix, and Jolly Ranchers. These delicious, dyed quartzite rounds on pink metal are embellished with a triple flourish on top. Length: 1.75"

name: G.S.B. Pearl Earrings

Freshwater pearls are beautiful and come in a variety of colors. This set of earrings features naturally "faceted" pearls in gold, silver and bronze on black metal.

name: Nouveau Earrings

Descending set of matching earrings celebrating modern art deco.  Copper, natural abalone lentil, patina metal, and river shell make for a unique but beautiful grouping.

name: Key Westerner Earrings

Key West, Florida -- a small island awash in the tropical colors of paradise. "Sugar apple" peridot and "blood orange" aventurine rounds over crystal clear ocean water quartzite coins.

name: Nude Jade Earrings

name: Pink Nebulae Earrings

Set of matching space themed earrings. Quartzite and lampwork beads in orange and pink on light pink metal.

name: Strawberry Pear Chardonnay Dessert Wine
description: *** This Product Is NOT for Sale *** However, my "extended family" can notify me and come over and drink it with me! This 2013 wine was vinted in southern California using French white grape juice, pear juice and strawberry purée. The wine was double-fermented in a two stage process and has aged for less than three months. A very limited run of only two cases were bottled. This was a study in sweet wines, sugar content and fermentation. The taste is quite sweet, with overtones of pear and florals and subtle notes of strawberry and caramel--and not at all dry. The strong but sweet smell is somewhat deceptive, as the drink-ability is determined more by the sugar content than the alcohol. Overall this is wine is more popular with women than men, but is worth a taste no matter who you are. A couple sips after dinner is a nice way to end the meal. I hope to share a glass with you. ---------------------------------------------- * - By adding this item to your cart, you are 21 years of age or older and would like to consume this with me in person. Your $1 order will be to verify that and get me to contact you! Of course, I can't sell wine, but we can enjoy it together! :D
